  "statement": "# Plus One\n\nThe array stores a non-negative integer digit by digit. Return the digits after adding one.\n\n## Examples\n\n**Example 1**\n\n```text\nInput: digits = [1,2,3]\nOutput: [1,2,4]\n```\n\n**Example 2**\n\n```text\nInput: digits = [9,9]\nOutput: [1,0,0]\n```\n\n**Example 3**\n\n```text\nInput: digits = [0]\nOutput: [1]\n```\n\n## Constraints\n\n- Inputs are sized for local offline execution.\n- Return the value described by the method signature.",
  "editorial": "Use direct arithmetic, matrix indexing, or bit operations to preserve the required invariants while keeping extra state small.",
  "solution_notes": "```python\nclass Solution:\n    def plusOne(self, digits):\n        for i in range(len(digits) - 1, -1, -1):\n            if digits[i] < 9:\n                digits[i] += 1; return digits\n            digits[i] = 0\n        return [1] + digits\n```",
  "hints": [
